
[1]nursery

   NURS'ERY, n.

   1. The place or apartment in a house appropriated to the care of
   children.

   2. A place where young trees are propagated for the purpose of being
   transplanted; a plantation of young trees.

   3. The place where any thing is fostered and the growth promoted.

   To see fair Padua, nursery of arts.

   So we say , a nursery of thieves or of rogues. Ale houses and
   dram-shops are the nurseries of intemperance.

   Christian families are the nurseries of the church on earth, as she is
   the nursery of the church in heaven.

   4. Taht which forms and educates. Commerce is the nursery of seamen.

   5. The act of nursing. [Little used.]

   6. That which is the object of a nurse's care.
